ZH: 外面的雾很浓。
EN: The fog outside is very thick.

ZH: 雾气笼罩着整个城市。
EN: The fog envelops the entire city.

ZH: 雾霾影响了空气质量。
EN: The haze affects air quality.

ZH: 雾中人影朦胧。
EN: Figures are vague in the mist.

ZH: 大雾导致了航班延误。
EN: Heavy fog has led to flight delays.

ZH: 雾化器可以使药物进入呼吸道。
EN: Nebulizers can deliver medication to the respiratory tract.

ZH: 他们消失在了雾中。
EN: They disappeared into the fog.

ZH: 寒风和雾一起袭来。
EN: The cold wind and fog came together.

ZH: 雾气在山谷中弥漫。
EN: The fog fills the valley.

ZH: 我迷失在了浓雾之中。
EN: I got lost in the thick fog.

ZH: 雾里看花。
EN: To see through fog and perceive flowers - to have a superficial understanding of things.

ZH: 因为雾太大，他无法开车。
EN: Because of the heavy fog, he couldn't drive.

ZH: 到处弥漫着薄雾。
EN: Thin mist pervades everything.

ZH: 我们在雾中迷了路。
EN: We got lost in the fog.

ZH: 他的思绪迷失在雾中。
EN: His thoughts lost in the mist.

ZH: 雾气中渐渐出现一座城堡。
EN: A castle gradually appeared in the fog.

ZH: 迷雾中的小径通往何方？
EN: Where does the path in the mist lead?

ZH: 雾气缭绕四周，看不清周围的景物。
EN: The fog enveloped everything, making it hard to see the surroundings.

ZH: 雾笼罩的山脚下是一个安静的村庄。
EN: The fog-covered foothills hid a quiet village.

ZH: 雾是河流的故事，河流被橄榄色的雾笼罩。
EN: The fog was a story of rivers, the rivers shrouded in olive-colored fog.
